            <!-- How to Get Started with KineMaster Lite -->
            <section id="getting-started">
                <h2>How to Get Started with KineMaster Lite</h2>
                <ol>
                    <li><strong>Download and Install:</strong> Search for KineMaster Lite in the Google Play Store or Apple App Store, then download and install the app.</li>
                    <li><strong>Import Media:</strong> Start a new project, choose your aspect ratio, and import videos, photos, or audio files.</li>
                    <li><strong>Basic Editing Functions:</strong> Cut, trim, split, and splice clips; add text, images, and effects.</li>
                    <li><strong>Add Effects and Transitions:</strong> Use the effects and transitions features to enhance your video.</li>
                    <li><strong>Voiceovers and Background Music:</strong> Add and adjust audio elements to complement your video.</li>
                    <li><strong>Export the Final Video:</strong> Choose resolution and quality settings, then export or share your video.</li>
                </ol>
                <p>Follow these steps to start creating professional-quality videos with KineMaster Lite, regardless of your editing experience.</p>
